-- Chelsea Closes on $13 Million Deal for Markovic: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-12-10T10:52:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-10/chelsea-closes-on-13-million-deal-for-markovic-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the web.  Serbian Target  Chelsea is close to signing 18-year-old Partizan Belgrade
midfielder Lazar Markovic for 8 million pounds ($12.8 million),
the  Daily Mail  reported.  Markovic has six goals in 12 games for Partizan, which
wants the fee to rise to as much as 14 million pounds if the
teenager meets appearance targets, the Mail said.  Mancini ‘Rage’  Manchester City coach  Roberto Mancini  “flew into a
dressing-room rage” after his team lost to Manchester United on
an injury-time goal yesterday,  the Sun  reported.  Mancini criticized goalkeeper Joe Hart as well as  Mario
Balotelli ,  Carlos Tevez  and Samir Nasri, the Sun added.  Henry III  Thierry Henry could start his third stint as an Arsenal
player in an F.A. Cup game against Swansea on Jan. 6, the  Daily
Mail  reported.  The Gunners are in advanced talks with New York Red Bulls
over taking 35-year-old Henry on loan, the Mail said.  Newcastle Move  Newcastle is likely to renew its interest in France right-
back Mathieu Debuchy during the January transfer window, the
 Daily Telegraph  reported.  The Magpies are also scouting Blackpool’s Thomas Ince and
looking for a new striker, the Telegraph said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
